body:
Rodrick Brown wrote:
> 
> use Data::Dumper;
> my %h;
> map { $h{$_->[0]}=$_->[1] } map { [ split/=/,$_ ] } split/\n/,$test;
> print Dumper(\%h);

Or, more intelligibly,

  my %h;

  foreach (split /\n/, $test) {
    my ($key, $val) = split /=/;
    $h{$key} = $val;
  }

Rob

